  "texts": [
    "Once well trained, it can predict the labels of the new samples with satisfactory performance.According to the application scenarios, SL can be categorized into the classification and regression.",
    "For classification models, their output results are categories or discrete values.",
    "The popular classification models are the K-nearest neighbor [185], decision tree [186], naive Bayes [187], support vector machine [188], and DNN [189].",
    "For example, the support vector machine focuses on finding a hyperplane to distinguish different categories of samples via optimization.",
    "In contrast, the regression models are usually leveraged to predict the continuous values, and the common regression models are logistic regression [190] and DNN [191]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
